==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lipochrin
<hw>Lip"o*chrin</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧p"⟦osl⟧*kr⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>li`pos</grk> fat + <grk>chro`a</grk> color.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A yellow coloring matter, soluble in
ether, contained in the small round fat drops in the retinal epithelium
cells. It is best obtained from the eyes of frogs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lipogram</ent>⟦br⟧
